## Research Report: MyOrdersRewardProgram Screen - DS Components and Store

### 1. CardVehicleTags Component

**Location**: `/Users/anotonio.silva/dev/rnm-app-fintech-rewardprogram/node_modules/@semparar/design-system-app/src/atomic/molecules/Cards/CardVehicleTags/`

**Component Structure**:
- Main entry point: `index.tsx` - dispatches to V1 or V2 based on `version` prop
- V2 implementation: `V2/view.tsx` (used in MyOrdersRewardProgram with `version="2.0"`)
- Models: `Models/index.ts`

**Key Features** (V2):
- Renders a card with icon, vehicle name, title/description, date, status tag, and ghost button
- Three type variants: `'actived' | 'cancel' | 'extended'` (MyOrdersRewardProgram uses `'extended'`)
- Uses `TagLabel` component for status display with color variants
- Built with atomic components: `Box`, `Icon`, `Text`, `TouchBox`, `SeparatorHorizontal`
- Supports customizable colors for vehicle name and ghost button text

**Props Interface** (`PropsCardVehicleTags`):
```typescript
{
  testID?: string;
  version?: '1.0' | '2.0';
  type?: 'actived' | 'cancel' | 'extended';
  icon: PropsIconsNameCore;
  iconColor?: PropsTokenColorsCore;
  vehicleName: string;
  vehicleNameColor?: 'BRAND_COMPLEMENT_01' | 'INTENSE_COLOR_04';
  title?: string;
  titleDescription?: string;
  statusTitle?: string;
  status: string;
  typeTag?: TypesTagLabel;  // 'success' | 'error' | 'alert' | 'highlight'
  highlightTag?: boolean;
  date?: string;
  dateNumber?: string;
  ghostButtonText?: string;
  ghostButtonTextColor?: 'BRAND_BASE_01' | 'BRAND_COMPLEMENT_01' | 'INTENSE_COLOR_05';
  onGhostButtonPress?: () => void;
  disabledGhostButtonPress?: boolean;
  hasStroke?: boolean;
  hideDividerBottom?: boolean;
  mt/mb/ml/mr?: spacing tokens;
}
```

**How MyOrdersRewardProgram uses it**:
```typescript
<CardVehicleTags
  vehicleName={item.description}
  icon={item.icon as PropsIconsNameCore}
  title="Valor em pontos"
  titleDescription={String(Math.abs(item.amount))}
  date="Data do resgate"
  dateNumber={formatDate(item.date)}
  statusTitle="Status do pedido"
  status={item.status}
  ghostButtonText="Exibir detalhes"
  onGhostButtonPress={() => handleDetailsOrders(...)}
  type="extended"
  typeTag={STATUS_COLORS[item.status] ?? 'alert'}
  version="2.0"
/>
```

---

